                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Robertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-11T13:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 11, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2139. According to telegram dated Dec[?] from Ward, it was expected that Ining
                    delegates would return to Tihwa within next few days (2068, Nov 30 to Dept,
                    repeated Moscow). Exceptional diplomatic talent of Liu Tse-jung and marked
                    ability of Chang Chih-chung (sent Dept, repeated Moscow) together with Soviet
                    Consul’s evident sincerity in use of good offices, makes it seem reasonable to
                    Ward to hope for satisfactory conclusion of conversations within next
                    fortnight.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
